PrecisAmendment to the FOOD AND DRUG REGULATIONS Schedule No. 760 requiring that all drugs for internal use containing acetylsalicylic acid (ASA) be labelled with a caution that children and teenagers should not use this medicine before a physician or pharmacist is consulted about Reye's syndrome.
